blog.name: spitchcraft
blog.title: Hey
blog.description: if ur here checking out my blog cuz I’m posting fallout 76 hate, just know that I post the hate because I’m heartbroken and I have to vent to make myself feel better somehow. I’ve been a lifelong Beth fan and watching one baffling dumpster fire after another happen in the wake of 76 is really awful to watch. Please understand, I’ve wanted to work for them since I was little, so the business practices on display are really disheartening. I was so excited to build settlements with my friends, and the game looks gorgeous, but I can’t bring myself to buy it anymore. The whole ordeal has really soured the pot for me specifically, but I’m very happy that other people can enjoy the game. It’s just not for me anymore.

Not that i’m not interested on the game, i’ve just never been a person that watched teasers of gameplay demos - i prefer checking out the thing when we get it, instead of following the hype devs try to build up.
